This project is part of a hands-on course focused on building real-world applications using Natural Language Processing (NLP) techniques in Python. Through a series of applied projects, I gained practical experience in transforming raw text data into actionable insights using a variety of industry-standard tools and methods.

üîç What I Learned & Implemented:

Text Preprocessing & Feature Extraction
I worked with techniques like tokenization, Bag of Words (BoW), and TF-IDF to convert unstructured text into structured numerical representations for machine learning models. These are foundational skills for any NLP pipeline.

Real-World Project Experience
The course included three major projects:

Sentiment analysis on Amazon product reviews ‚Äì to understand customer opinions using NLP.

Stock market trend prediction ‚Äì applying data science techniques to financial text data.

Brand strength prediction ‚Äì combining textual and numerical data to forecast brand positioning.

Data Analysis & Visualization
I used Pandas and NumPy for data manipulation, and Matplotlib & Seaborn for visual storytelling, helping to interpret model results and identify data trends.

Machine Learning Integration
I applied models using Scikit-learn, implementing classification techniques and evaluating model performance using metrics like accuracy, precision, recall, and confusion matrices.

Stakeholder Communication
Beyond the technical work, I practiced communicating insights clearly‚Äîtranslating model outputs into simple, actionable findings for non-technical audiences.

